HEADWORD: Endoss
<hw>En*doss"</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>endosser</ets>. See <er>Endorse</er>.]</ety> <def>To put upon the
back or outside of anything; -- the older spelling of
<xex>endorse</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
